Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I go to Page 11 of Head MRI
Then 'Normal imaging of facial skeleton and brain case' radio button is enabled
And 'Finding' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Temporal bone' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'I describe' radio button is enabled and preselected
And 'I know' radio button is enabled
And 'Localization' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Differential diagnosis' tab is enabled

When I select 'Localization' tab
And I select 'I know' radio button
Then 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled
And 'Both sides' radio button is enabled

And 'Inner ear (labyrinth)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ductus endolymphaticus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Saccus endolymphaticus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Internal acoustic canal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Porus acusticus internus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Middle ear (tympanum)' checkbox is enabled
And 'External acoustic canal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Temporal bone apex' checkbox is enabled

And 'Auricle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Mastoid' checkbox is enabled
And 'Foramen stylomastoideum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tuba auditiva' checkbox is enabled
And 'Facial nerve canal' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Right' radio button
Then 'Right' radio button is selected

When I select 'Left' radio button
Then 'Left' radio button is selected

When I select 'Both sides' radio button
Then 'Both sides' radio button is selected
And 'Symmetrical' radio button is enabled
And 'Asymmetrical' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Inner ear (labyrinth)' checkbox
And I select 'Ductus endolymphaticus' checkbox
And I select 'Saccus endolymphaticus' checkbox
And I select 'Internal acoustic canal' checkbox
And I select 'Porus acusticus internus' checkbox
And I select 'External acoustic canal' checkbox
And I select 'Temporal bone apex' checkbox
Then all the above checkboxes are selected

When I select 'Middle ear (tympanum)' checkbox
Then 'Middle ear (tympanum)' checkbox is selected
And 'Epitympanon' checkbox is enabled
And 'Mesotympanum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hypotympanon' checkbox is enabled
 When I select 'Epitympanon' checkbox
And I select 'Mesotympanum' checkbox
And I select 'Hypotympanon' checkbox
Then all the 3 checkboxes are selected

When I select 'Auricle' checkbox
And I select 'Foramen stylomastoideum' checkbox
And I select 'Tuba auditiva' checkbox
And I select 'Facial nerve canal' checkbox
Then all the above checkboxes are selected

When I select 'Mastoid' checkbox
Then 'Mastoid' checkbox is selected
And 'Antrum' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Antrum' checkbox
Then 'Antrum' checkbox is selected
